"""Pinned per-table DuckDB schemas for Synapse profiler extracts.

These exist because the SQL pool extracts append across runs (and across pools
within a run) using watermarks; pandas dtype inference can drift between
batches when columns are null-only in one batch but typed in the next.
Declaring an explicit schema keeps DuckDB in charge of the column types and
lets it cast incoming data on insert.
"""

